Lagos State Governor, Mr. Babajide Sanwo-Olu has said the state is making investments in strategic economic development to help build and grow businesses, as well as tackle emerging challenges. Speaking during the graduation for 1,140 unemployed youths trained under the Information Technology (IT)-enabled entrepreneurship skills and mentorship programme of the Ministry of Wealth Creation and Employment, the governor reiterated the state’s readiness to deliver  results by supporting the youth to create vibrant economies in the communities.   Xiaomi 12 series redefines flagship category     Nigeria, others pay highest for data     Fed Govt inaugurates committee to review Nigeria’s…   Represented by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Mrs Sherifat Folashade Jaji, noted that the government was executing an aggressive strategy for knowledge exchange and capacity development training for youths in the startup and social entrepreneurship scene, adding that everything would be done to enable them to turn their ideas into reality through innovation and entrepreneurship. According to him, the talent discovery and IT-enabled entrepreneurship skills and mentorship programme, which took place in the 57 local government/local council development area was  done   to address the  need to equip its young with the skill set and mindset that will help them excel in jobs of the digital world. Through a public-private-partnership with Digital Age Consultants, he said the programme aims to transform youths from users of digital technology to producers.